<exercise checkit-seed="0002" checkit-slug="P2" checkit-title="Probability with Or/Not">
    <statement>
        <p>
            
                <p>
                    A board is laid out in a grid. The top is broken into columns, labeled A to E, and the side is broken into rows, labeled 1 to 6. If you pick a spot on the board at random, what is the probability that the spot
                    <ol>
                        <li> is in columns D to E or is in rows 2 to 5? </li>
                        <li> is not in columns D to E? </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            
                <p>
                    <ol>
                        <li> The probability that the spot is in columns D to E or is in rows 2 to 5 is <me>\frac{2}{5} + \frac{4}{6} - \frac{8}{30} = \cdots = \frac{4}{5}</me> </li>
                        <li> The probability that the spot is not in columns D to E is <me>1 - \frac{2}{5} = \cdots = \frac{3}{5}</me></li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
